OL,3,CGovernment asylum housing plans to
OL,4,Ccost millions more than hotels `
OL,5,Cwatchdog
OL,7,FHead of the NAO Gareth Davies said:
OL,8,F"The Home Office has made progress in
OL,9,Freducing the use of hotels for asylum
OL,10,Faccommodation. Yet the pace at which
OL,11,Fthe Government pursued its plans led
OL,12,Fto increased risks, and it now expects
OL,13,Flarge sites to cost more than using
OL,14,Fhotel accommodation."
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@UO]
