OL,4,Ccost millions more than hotels `
OL,5,Cwatchdog
OL,7,FBut the Home Office insisted its plan
OL,8,Fwas better value for money for the
OL,9,Ftaxpayer than continuing to use hotels.
OL,11,FWhile the Government has "made
OL,12,Fprogress" by cutting the number of
OL,13,Fhotels to house asylum seekers, and
OL,14,Fhad stopped using 60 by the end of
OL,15,FJanuary, it has "incurred losses and
OL,16,Fincreased risk" by "rapidly
OL,17,Fprogressing its plans to establish
OL,18,Flarge sites", the NAO said.
OL,26,@sD@ZOUtD@IO]wD@QOUxD@OO]xD@TOUzD@LO]
